      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "I got a bit carried away with the metaphor. To simplify, when lactic acid levels rise, it disrupts the normal ionic balance inside the muscle cells, leading to an increase in intracellular calcium concentrations. This triggers the activation of various signaling pathways, including the release of histamine and other chemical mediators. These mediators bind to pain receptors, such as TRPV1, which are responsible for detecting changes in pH, temperature, and other stimuli. The binding of these mediators to their receptors sends signals to the brain, which interprets them as pain, resulting in the sensation of burning or discomfort.",
